# Trivy waivers — neo4j image only (wired to the neo4j scan step in
# .github/workflows/ci.yml via the `trivyignores:` input; NOT applied to the
# pgvector or ollama scans, which stay strict).
#
# Context (Issue #2): the neo4j base image is pinned to
# neo4j:5.26.25-community-ubi10. Switching from the Debian (`-trixie`) base to
# Red Hat UBI-10 already eliminated all 14 HIGH/CRITICAL OS-package CVEs
# (including 2 CRITICAL gnutls) — those are NOT waived, they are fixed by the
# base choice. What remains are 3 HIGH CVEs in the netty jars that Neo4j 5.26.25
# bundles itself. They are identical across every base variant and cannot be
# fixed without a new Neo4j release that bumps netty to >= 4.1.133.Final.
#
# Why these are acceptable for THIS deployment (spec §6.7 accept-with-justification):
#   - Story Forge runs Neo4j bound to 127.0.0.1 only, single trusted user,
#     non-root container, no-new-privileges. There is no untrusted network peer.
#   - None of the three is data-disclosure or RCE. Two are denial-of-service
#     (resource exhaustion); the third is an HTTP client-codec response-desync
#     bug reachable only when Neo4j acts as an outbound HTTP client against a
#     malicious server — a path this deployment never exercises.
#   - All three are fixed in netty 4.1.133.Final (released 2026-05-04). Drop this
#     file the moment a Neo4j 5.26.x patch ships that bundle; re-scan should pass
#     clean with no waiver.
#
# All waivers across images are also indexed in infra/trivy/WAIVERS.md (the
# review register: fixed-in versions + drop conditions, checked periodically).
#
# Revisit: each Neo4j patch bump (next time the image tag is updated).

# CVE-2026-42583 — netty-codec (Lz4FrameDecoder): a stream of small LZ4 frames
# forces repeated large buffer allocation -> memory exhaustion (DoS). Fixed in
# 4.1.133.Final by enforcing maxDecompressedLength.
CVE-2026-42583

# CVE-2026-42584 — netty-codec-http (HttpClientCodec): response desynchronization
# mis-pairing pipelined HEAD/GET with 1xx responses (client-side parsing bug,
# not DoS). Not reachable: we do not drive Neo4j as an HTTP client.
CVE-2026-42584

# CVE-2026-42587 — netty-codec-http (HttpContentDecompressor): maxAllocation
# bypass via br/zstd/snappy Content-Encoding -> decompression-bomb DoS. Fixed in
# 4.1.133.Final.
CVE-2026-42587
